         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/7/84 ¶ The enclosed Lycopodium, dear Sir Joseph, was sent to me as distinct from L. Phlegmaria by Mr Bailey. It seems to me very doubtful whether it can be regarded as anything more than an extreme...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.07.28a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-1890, f. 114.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/7/84<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated</seg>: Thank for further [duplicate].</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The enclosed Lycopodium, dear Sir Joseph, was sent to me as distinct from L. Phlegmaria by Mr Bailey. It seems to me very doubtful whether it can be regarded as anything more than an extremely robust form of that species. But as I am still working away from my office at Dr Büttner’s mansion,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Alexander Büttner.</p>
               </note> I have neither the material for comparison readily available, nor Mr Baker’s essays on <name key="Lycopodiaceae">Lycopodiaceae</name> accessible. Perhaps you would give me your or his opinion on this particular plant. I hope Mr Bakers writings on the <name key="Lycopodiaceae">Lycopodiaceae</name> can appear in a connected form; it is very inconvenient to use them in their present scattered state of publication.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>ferd. von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The sheet is annotated below M's signature:</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">In J.G. Baker's hand</seg>: This precisely agrees with a typical specimen of the Lycopodium phlegmaroides of Gaudichaud, figured Freycin. Voyage t. 23 [Freycinet &amp; Gaudichaud (1826-30), text p. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>281, Atlas, t. 23] but it is scarcely I think worth separating specifically from Phlegmaria. We have several specimens just like to from Fiji; Gaudichaud's type is from Rawak. J. G. Baker Kew herb. Oct 15 1884.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">In D. Oliv</seg>
                     <seg style="">er</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">'s</seg>
                     <seg style=""> </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">hand</seg>: house for Kew.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
